               THe Ciuile lawes commit the tuition of orphanes to the next of their bloud, whether the kinred grow on the fathers ſyde or on the mothers ſyde, that is to ſaye, to euerye man accordynge to the degree and order, wherein his tourne is nexte to ſucceede the pupille in his inhertiaūce. And the reaſon of this lawe is that: that no man will beehaue him ſelfe more tenderly or more fauourably in the carefull education of the infaunte, thenne hee that is nexte of hys bloude.

